Description¶

Utility functions for inspecting Qt objects

msTools.coreUI.qt.inspect_utils.getReadablePropertiesFromClass(qtClass)¶

Return readable properties from a given Qt class.

Readable properties are those which can be accessed via PySide2.QtCore.QObject.property(). Refer to The Property System for details.

Parameters:qtClass (T <= type) – A non-strict subclass of PySide2.QtCore.QObject.
Returns:list [basestring] – The readable properties for objects of qtClass.
msTools.coreUI.qt.inspect_utils.getReadablePropertiesFromObject(qtObject)¶

Return readable properties from a given Qt object.

Readable properties are those which can be accessed via PySide2.QtCore.QObject.property(). Refer to The Property System for details.

Parameters:qtObject (T <= PySide2.QtCore.QObject) – A Qt object.
Returns:list [basestring] – The readable properties from qtObject.
msTools.coreUI.qt.inspect_utils.getWidget(widgetName, widgetClass=None)¶

Retrieve a widget by name and class.

Note

Name hierarchies such as "parent|child" are not supported. Therefore the first widget with the given name will be returned.

Parameters:
  • widgetName (basestring) – A non-hierarchical widget name.
  • widgetClass (T <= type) – A non-strict subclass of PySide2.QtWidgets.QWidget.
Raises:

RuntimeError – If a widget could not be identified for the given widgetName and widgetClass.
Returns:

PySide2.QtWidgets.QWidget – A widget which was found to have a name corresponding to widgetName and type corresponding to widgetClass.
